<p>Argentines held midterm congressional elections to judge President Javier Milei&#x27;s austerity and pro-market agenda and to decide whether he can secure the legislative support needed to advance his program . The vote also carried international stakes: U.S. President Trump signaled that future U.S. assistance could depend on the outcome, raising the prospect of foreign financing shifting with electoral results . Campaigning and polls reflected voter anxiety about the economy, recent scandals involving Milei&#x27;s circle, and doubts about his ability to govern effectively for the next two years .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/cGmUsHfFJ2o9UPz1LdPeQlv_xS_BcdG371S8HPcgFBJDs605nuxdj7VvSLoVSD2oHzu-mvv2T3vptJ1-YkOR_07Q8FbPvuurTC6qOIxgox1y9dm9UxA0Rvib3-8HHf3c5YckjyGAAGihSVy22hitrvRHLITFCdzY7eQE6wfBJRSgi85vuWtYQCI1gH7wlvRjJzVxRaYDosFihqP719bE6rZ3p1KFKHkludE' alt='President Javier Milei of Argentina in the city of Rosario on Thursday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Market reaction: Financial markets prepared for volatility ahead of the vote, with traders and analysts warning that results could influence currency stability and investor confidence in Argentina&#x27;s economic program .</li><li>Seats at stake: The midterms were for half the Chamber of Deputies and one-third of the Senate, contests that will shape Milei&#x27;s ability to pass major legislation .</li><li>Political image: Milei&#x27;s image as an outsider has been dented by a string of scandals and setbacks that gave opposition groups momentum in the run-up to the vote .</li><li>Opposition gains: Opposition parties campaigned on economic relief and political stability, and several reports said they had gained ground in polls, altering the arithmetic Milei faces in Congress .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Javier Milei and allies: Supporters framed the midterms as a referendum on rapid free-market reforms and austerity measures intended to stabilise the economy and end chronic currency turmoil. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/argentina-votes-in-crucial-test-of-mileis-reforms/a-74500159'>DW</a>)</li><li>Opposition parties: Opposition leaders argued voters were fatigued by economic pain and recent scandals, and they positioned themselves as offering greater political stability and protection from harsh austerity. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251026-what-to-know-about-argentina-s-mid-term-vote-a-key-test-for-trump-ally-milei'>France 24</a>)</li><li>United States / President Trump: U.S. President Trump publicly linked future U.S. assistance to Argentina with the outcome of the midterms, saying support could be contingent on Milei&#x27;s political strength. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/argentina-votes-in-midterm-elections-set-to-test-president-mileis-mandate-and-us-support/article70204300.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/argentina-votes-in-crucial-test-of-milei-s-reforms/a-74500159'>Argentina votes in crucial test of Milei&#x27;s reforms</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/9492ca39-1cfe-451a-83df-ff4a340bbb15'>Markets brace as Argentines go to the polls</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/argentina-votes-in-midterm-elections-set-to-test-president-mileis-mandate-and-us-support/article70204300.ece'>Argentina votes in midterm elections set to test President Milei&#x27;s mandate and U.S. support</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/26/world/americas/argentina-election-javier-milei.html'>What to Know About Argentinaâ€™s Midterm Election</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/argentina-votes-midterm-elections-set-test-president-mileis-126872151'>Argentina votes in midterm elections set to test President Milei&#x27;s mandate and US support</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251026-wh